net.tmachine.gpg4
Interface iModule

All Known Implementing Classes:
bModule, RequestProcessor, SimpleRequestCacher
public interface iModule

This defines an FSM (finite state machine) for the status of a running module on a server.

This is a convenience interface that I use for all server projects (although this is a cut-down version without many of the more advanced features, like pausing). Several of the states are not used at all in this example, and if you want to use an FSM in production code, you should really plan a more appropriate one than this simple example!

static int RUNNING
          Service is now considered to be "up and running" and fully working, accepting connections, etc
static int STARTING
          moving from STOPPED to RUNNING
static int STOPPED
          instantiated but refusing requests, not active, ready to enter STARTING, perhaps has previously been in running state
static int STOPPING
          moving from RUNNING to STOPPED
static int UNLOADED
          Cannot return to any other states; this is usually a prelude to the class files being unloaded, and/or the entire server being shutdown.
static int UNLOADING
          being de-referenced, shutting down permanently, cannot return to any other state from this one
